def _unstack_multiple(data, clocs, fill_value=None):
    if len(clocs) == 0:
        return data

    index = data.index

    clocs = [index._get_level_number(i) for i in clocs]
    rlocs = [i for i in range(index.nlevels) if i not in clocs]

    if any(index.get_level_values(i).nunique() > 1 for i in clocs):
        raise ValueError("Hierarchical columns are not supported yet")

    result = data.copy()
    for i in range(len(clocs)):
        level = index.get_level_values(clocs[i])
        new_level = pd.Categorical(level, categories=level.unique()).codes
        result = result.set_index(level, append=True)
        result.index = result.index.droplevel(clocs[i])
